From Roger Walls Subject Re Boom Dog attack In article Dan Sorenson writes Ryan Cousineau writes mere or so gravel road with few loose rocks on it as in just like bad concrete and of swinging beef jumped a fence came out of the ditch and rammed me When I saw her jump the fence I went for the gas since she was about feet ahead of me but a good forty to the Damn cow literally chased me down and nailed No damage to cow a bent case guard and a severely annoyed rider were the only If I had my shotgun I'd still be eating Nope if of cow can hit me when I'm actively evading forget a much more manueverable Just run them One day out riding my friend and i were passing a field of goats and noticed out on the As we slowed to pass the ram made a dash at my friend just missing him and then tangling it self up in the barb wire Being good samaritains and generally nice guys we turned around to untrangle the goat from the barbed As I pulled up next to him seeing him still tangled up stopped the bike and got off the Goat had vanished into the field I guess Jolly Roger